==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: bogbean
<hw>bogbean</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a perennial plant of Europe and
America (<spn>Menyanthes trifoliata</spn>) having racemes of white or
purplish flowers and intensely bitter trifoliate leaves; often rooting
at the water margin and spreading across the surface; -- called also
<altname>bog myrtle</altname>, <altname>water shamrock</altname> and
<altname>marsh trefoil</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> water shamrock, buckbean, bog myrtle, marsh
trefoil.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bogberry</ent>⟦br⟧
